                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.512/44.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s telegram April 22. I consider that the temporary withholding of
                    consent to stamp tax would still be useful as a means of securing complete
                    observance by China of our treaty rights in respect to inland taxation. See my
                    despatch No. 588.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
